#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:1
msgid "Adding New Intrinsics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:3
msgid ""
"So you want to teach cuda-oxide a new GPU trick. Maybe NVIDIA just shipped a "
"new instruction, or you need an existing PTX operation that nobody has wired "
"up yet. Good news: the process is mechanical. Five crates, five steps, and "
"roughly thirty minutes once you have done it before."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:8
msgid ""
"This chapter walks through the full pipeline using two real examples -- one "
"trivially simple, one with a few twists -- so you can see exactly what "
"happens at each stage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:14
msgid "The Five-Stage Pipeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:16
msgid "Every GPU intrinsic follows the same path through the compiler:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:18
msgid ""
"cuda-device          User writes:  thread::threadIdx_x()\n"
"    │\n"
"    ▼\n"
"mir-importer       Compiler sees the call, emits a `dialect-nvvm` op\n"
"    │\n"
"    ▼\n"
"dialect-nvvm       The op lives here as a verified IR node\n"
"    │\n"
"    ▼\n"
"mir-lower          Converts the `dialect-nvvm` op into an LLVM dialect op\n"
"    │\n"
"    ▼\n"
"llvm-export        Exports textual LLVM IR  →  llc turns it into PTX\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:34
msgid "At the `mir-lower` stage you pick one of two strategies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:0
msgid "Strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:0
msgid "When to use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/adding-new-intrinsics.md:0
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

